    body_html: `<p class="article-lead">Environmental design, flavour sequencing and conversation structure — how to turn your flat into the best date venue you'll ever visit. No reservations. No Ubers. No compromise on quality.</p>
<h2>The Problem With "Staying In"</h2>
<p>Staying in has a perception problem. It sounds like settling. The truth is a well-designed home experience can do things a restaurant never can: total control of environment, zero interruption, and freedom to move between activities without a check-in time. The difference between an evening that feels special and one that doesn't isn't the venue. It's the intention.</p>
